snippet.textDisplay: Idk wtf type of Heads up 7 up yall played, but mine WAS a game. 7 people were chosen and went to the front. Everyone else put their heads down and put their thumbs up. snippet.textDisplay: Heads up 7 up is a game. You have seven pickers and everyone else puts their heads down and thumbs up. The pickers pick people by touching their thumbs and then someone “usually the teacher, aka me” says “heads up 7 up” and the people picked stand up and try to guess who picked them. It’s a game I sometimes play with my seventh graders when we have five extra minutes and I don’t want them to be on their phones. We don’t play it a lot though, because by seventh grade they’re kind of over it.
